(28, 1, '2023-03-25 12:17:55', '2023-03-25 12:17:55', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Do you have all the necessary barista accessories at home and still think that a cup of coffee from a cafe simply tastes better?¬†Definitely don\'t let that put you off.¬†Maybe you need to slightly adjust the preparation procedure or subtly change the way you work with the coffee machine.¬†We are absolutely sure that you too can achieve the best coffee at home.¬†We will advise you how to do it.¬†In this article, you will learn 4 tips that, if you follow them, will ensure you a perfect espresso and milk foam.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>BASIC PILLARS OF PROPER COFFEE PREPARATION</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The basis of a barista\'s success are three absolutely simple pillars ‚Äì<strong>cleanliness, freshness and ratio¬†</strong>.¬†The overall quality of the resulting drink depends on these three criteria.¬†If you keep your coffee machine and other barista accessories clean, use freshly ground coffee and keep the right ratio between it and water, you will get the most important thing done.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The coffee maker should be&nbsp;<strong>cleaned every day&nbsp;</strong>.&nbsp;The deposits that the coffee leaves in his guts could turn rancid.&nbsp;At least the basic rinsing and daily maintenance of the coffee machine is therefore an absolutely necessary process.&nbsp;Likewise,&nbsp;<strong>balancing the ratio between ground coffee and water&nbsp;</strong>.&nbsp;Each preparation method has slightly different requirements, but if we were talking \"only\" about lever coffee machines, definitely remember that one shot of a standard espresso should flow through&nbsp;<strong>7 grams of coffee&nbsp;</strong>.&nbsp;But if you also like to prepare any drip coffee, read the correct proportions and preparation procedures<a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/blogs/novinky\">on our blog</a>.&nbsp;You will surely find your favorite method there.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And the freshness?&nbsp;We probably don\'t need to explain that to you.&nbsp;<strong>The freshness of the grains&nbsp;</strong>should share the first place together with the cleanliness.&nbsp;Coffee beans get old quickly and lose their taste.&nbsp;Ground coffee usually does not last more than a few hours.&nbsp;For grains, this time is considerably longer, but you should still process them within a week at the latest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These three pillars are linked to other points that need to be known and which will raise your barista skills to the next level.&nbsp;So read on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. BUY FRESHLY ROASTED WHOLE GRAINS</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Forget ground coffee from ordinary stores.¬†Excellent coffee, whether it is espresso or any other drip alternative, can only be prepared from high-quality and,¬†<strong>above all, fresh coffee beans¬†</strong>.¬†If you would put your trust in pre-ground coffee, definitely don\'t rely on it being fresh.¬†Regardless of the required coarseness of grinding, which is different for each preparation method, which will also greatly affect your final coffee experience.¬†You can buy ideal coffee, for example, at our cafes or¬†¬†<strong>from us</strong><a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/collections/nase-kava\"><strong>on the e-shop</strong></a>, where new coffee products are constantly added.¬†Here at Coffee Source, we have been roasting coffee for you every day for over 15 years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":125,\"width\":651,\"height\":434,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized is-style-default\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpresseng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/istockphoto-1339743849-170667a.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-125\" width=\"651\" height=\"434\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. GRIND ONLY AS MANY GRAINS AS YOU WILL USE IMMEDIATELY</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This point is really closely related to the previous one.¬†Once you get quality coffee beans, the grinder will, willy-nilly, become your right hand.¬†You can easily use that one as well<a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/collections/mleti/products/rucni-mlynek-nerez-basic\">small</a>, but from a practical point of view, one is definitely more advantageous<a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/collections/mleti/products/eureka-atom-specialty-65mm\">automatically</a>.¬†You can pre-set the roughness on it and then just grind using a button.¬†You can read about how to precisely grind coffee in our other article<a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/blogs/novinky/jak-precizne-namlit-kavu\">blog article</a>.¬†We are currently interested in how much coffee needs to be processed.¬†After all, if you\'re going to grind an entire packet of grains, we very much hope that you\'ll use it all up by the end of the day.¬†Because if not, the next day\'s cup of coffee definitely won\'t taste nearly as good.¬†Therefore, it is always necessary¬†<strong>to process only the amount that you need¬†</strong>.¬†After all, baristas in cafes also grind into each lever and for each customer separately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":129,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpresseng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/coffee-3465466__480.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-129\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. STORE COFFEE BEANS PROPERLY</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will stay with grains.&nbsp;Their storage is not quite like that.&nbsp;Whole grains also don\'t last forever, just a few days by default.&nbsp;However, you can keep them fresher for longer when you store them in a container that does not let in&nbsp;<strong>any sunlight&nbsp;</strong>and keeps its contents at about the&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>same temperature&nbsp;</strong>all the time.&nbsp;Well, we\'re not even talking about humidity.&nbsp;Therefore, containers with tight closures and rubberized edges are ideal.&nbsp;A suitable variant is also a coffee can from the Miir brand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also be careful about freezing coffee.&nbsp;In this way, you will not prolong its freshness, but you will immediately destroy it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":130,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpresseng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/steel-2595828__480.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-130\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4. FILTER THE WATER</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are now clear about the ratio of water and coffee.¬†However, so that the taste of your coffee is not negatively affected by anything, it is necessary to filter the used water.¬†<strong>In this way, you will rid it of all bad particles and limescale¬†</strong>, which most often has a hand in influencing the resulting taste.¬†We analyzed the importance of quality water in the coffee preparation process in more detail in<a href=\"https://coffeesource.eu/blogs/novinky/voda-zakladni-element-kavy\">this article of ours.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '4 proven tips for preparing the best coffee at home', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '4-proven-tips-for-preparing-the-best-coffee-at-home', '', '', '2023-03-25 20:23:43', '2023-03-25 20:23:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpresseng/?p=28', 0, 'post', '', 1),
